<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Survey</title>

	<link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/survey/Survey.css">
    <!--BOOTSTRAP Links-->
    <!-- CSS only -->
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-1BmE4kWBq78iYhFldvKuhfTAU6auU8tT94WrHftjDbrCEXSU1oBoqyl2QvZ6jIW3" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <!-- JavaScript Bundle with Popper -->
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-ka7Sk0Gln4gmtz2MlQnikT1wXgYsOg+OMhuP+IlRH9sENBO0LRn5q+8nbTov4+1p" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
    
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div id="surveyIntro">
            <h3>Survey for Chemical Twins app requirements</h3>
            <p>This is a survey made for the testing of the Chemical Twins web application, developed for a thesis project. <br>
            All the information from this survey will be used solely for the purpose of veryfing that the functionalities of the web application work. <br> 
            In case some of the functionalities don't work as intended then this survey will be used to fix those problems. <br> In order to take this survey please open a <a href="https://chemical-twins.herokuapp.com/" target="_blank">page to the web application</a>.</p>
            <label for="checkbox">Agree to the use of this data for the improvement of the application: </label>
            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="checkbox">
            <br><hr>
            <button onclick="loadSurvey()">Start Survey</button>
        </div>
        <div id="progressBar" style="display: none;">
            <div id="progress">0%</div>
        </div>
        <form action="./data/submit-survey" id="surveyForm" method="POST" style="display: none;">
            <div class="form-group questions" style="display: none;">
                <h3>Create an Account</h3>
                <p>Try to create an account in the web application with a unique email. You can do this by opening the navigation bar and by clicking on 'account'. <br>
                You'll be redirected to the page to create a new account. Once you do that a you should be redirected to the homepage and receive an email to verify your account.
                <br><br> Did it work?</p>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer1" id="answer1yes" value="yes">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer1">Yes</label>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer1" id="answer1no" value="no">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer1">No</label>
                <br><hr>
                <label for="answer1no_why">If 'No' then what went wrong?</label>
                <textarea class="form-control" id="justification" name="answer1no_why" rows="2"></textarea>
                <br><hr>
                <button onclick="nextQuestion()" type="button">Continue</button>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group questions" style="display: none;">
                <h3>Verify your Account</h3>
                <p>Now you should go to your emails and have a new email from <strong>chemicaltwinsrug@gmail.com</strong> with a link to 
                verify your account. Click on the link and you should be redirected to the homepage with a notification that your account is now verified.
                <br><br> Did it work?</p>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer2" id="answer2yes" value="yes">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer2">Yes</label>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer2" id="answer2no" value="no">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer2">No</label>
                <br><hr>
                <label for="answer2no_why">If 'No' then what went wrong?</label>
                <textarea class="form-control" id="justification" name="answer2no_why" rows="2"></textarea>
                <br><hr>
                <button onclick="nextQuestion()" type="button">Continue</button>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group questions" style="display: none;">
                <h3>Login</h3>
                <p>Now try to login the website with your email and password. To see that it worked open the navbar and you should see your username displayed there <br>
                along with some links that you weren't previously able to see.
                <br><br>
                Did it work?
                </p>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer3" id="answer3yes" value="yes">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer3">Yes</label>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer3" id="answer3no" value="no">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer3">No</label>
                <br><hr>
                <label for="answer3no_why">If 'No' then what went wrong?</label>
                <textarea class="form-control" id="justification" name="answer3no_why" rows="2"></textarea>
                <br><hr>
                <button onclick="nextQuestion()" type="button">Continue</button>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group questions" style="display: none;">
                <h3>Edit your account</h3>
                <p>Now that you've logged in your account you should be able to view different links on the navbar, one of those links goes to a page to edit your account. <br>
                Click on the link and try to change your username through that. Once you do open the navbar and you should see a different name displayed on top (your username)
                <br><br>
                Did it work?
                </p>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer4" id="answer4yes" value="yes">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer4">Yes</label>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer4" id="answer4no" value="no">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer4">No</label>
                <br><hr>
                <label for="answer4no_why">If 'No' then what went wrong?</label>
                <textarea class="form-control" id="justification" name="answer4no_why" rows="2"></textarea>
                <br><hr>
                <button onclick="nextQuestion()" type="button">Continue</button>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group questions" style="display: none;">
                <h3>Logout</h3>
                <p>Now open the navbar once more and logout from the website. You should be able to see a log out button. Click on it and you should logout from the website <br>
                To confirm that open the navbar once more and then you should't see your username anymore as well as the links to logout and edit your account
                <br><br>
                Did it work?
                </p>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer5" id="answer5yes" value="yes">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer5">Yes</label>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer5" id="answer5no" value="no">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer5">No</label>
                <br><hr>
                <label for="answer5no_why">If 'No' then what went wrong?</label>
                <textarea class="form-control" id="justification" name="answer5no_why" rows="2"></textarea>
                <br><hr>
                <button onclick="nextQuestion()" type="button">Continue</button>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group questions" style="display: none;">
                <h3>Password reset</h3>
                <p> Now, after you logged out the website, go again to the login page. Under login click on 'Click Here' to open a new form to reset your password. <br>
                Input the email you used to create the account and click on send email. Now go to your email inbox and check your new email from <strong>chemicaltwinsrug@gmail.com</strong> <br>
                This link should bring you to a new page where you can set a new password; do that and then try to login again with your new password.
                <br><br>
                Did it work?
                </p>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer6" id="answer6yes" value="yes">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer6">Yes</label>
                <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="answer5" id="answer6no" value="no">
                <label class="form-check-label" for="answer6">No</label>
                <br><hr>
                <label for="answer6no_why">If 'No' then what went wrong?</label>
                <textarea class="form-control" id="justification" name="answer6no_why" rows="2"></textarea>
                <br><hr>
                <button onclick="nextQuestion()" type="button">Continue</button>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group questions" style="display: none;">
                <p>How happy are u about the thing?</p>
                <input type="radio" name="answer4" value="1">1
                <input type="radio" name="answer4" value="2">2
                <input type="radio" name="answer4" value="3">3
                <input type="radio" name="answer4" value="4">4
                <input type="radio" name="answer4" value="5">5
                <br><hr>
                <button onclick="nextQuestion()" type="button">Finish</button>
            </div>
            <div id="finishSurvey" style="display: none;">
                <p>Thank u for partecipating in the survey, now the questions are over</p>
                <button>Submit your answers</button>
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
<script src="../js/survey/Survey.js"></script>
</html>